rComments: Two midterms, cumulative final and an 8-page case study term paper.  A lot of work for a lower div.  Some classes are quite engaging.   Avril knows her stuff.  TA's are friendly.

Exams ask for specific answers to vague/generic ?s.  If answer isn't what TA is looking for, even if correct=wrong. Studied book/lectures and this straight A student got a D on first midterm.   Test questions aren't framed in the same way Avril frames them in class for us to discuss, but I think she's starting to see that and direct better.

NOT taught as an INTRO to personality course.  I'm a graduating senior and this class should be a senior seminar the way she teaches it.  I've done research, field study, and will start graduate school in the fall and in this class, THE EXAMS ARE WAY TOO DIFFICULT. Study guide not specific. Exams ask for in-depth comprehension short answer.

I wasnt overly enthused about taking another developmental course,  but I could not be happier that I ended up in Avrils course. She makes the learning of her material fun & easy, & clearly really cares about what her students have to say. This class shouldn't be hard if you attend class & work hard, which are easy to do with such a great professor

Avril is amazing, kind, fair, understanding, hilarious, her lectures are organized and clear, she makes class engaging and enjoyable, she gives thorough studyguides for exams, she's helpful with answering questions, she actually cares about her students, and is willing to make adjustments to accommodate them (I earned an A).

Avril is amazing, kind, fair, understanding, hilarious, she makes class enjoyable and engaging, her lectures are organized and clear, she explains concepts well, provides thorough studyguides for exams, helpful with answering questions, she really cares about her students, and is willing to make adjustments to accommodate them (I earned an A).

She is very emersed in the subject of the class. She loves it and makes it interesting. The midterms were difficult even though I attended every class and did all of the reading. Just pay close attention and you should be fine. She tells good stories and the lectures are interesting and relevant to the psyc field.

Great class, but also a great teacher.  She wanted to bounce things between herself and the students.  Always happy to talk and answer questions.  Class was fun and informative.  She tested on what she went over.  More big idea oriented, rather then fact driven.  Take her!

I highly recommend taking a class w/ Avril. She treats her students like they could teach her something, too. She is very nice & approachable, & obviously is very interested in what she is teaching. Felt like a true learning environment, where everyone in class, including Avril, was trying to pool together to learn. THIS is how college should be!

Avril is awesome.  She's funny and makes you want to get involved in class discussion.  this was her first time teaching the course so we were all in for the same ride being that things were a bit unclear and unorganized, but it also made way for great discussions and ways to use the material

(Class formerly known as psyc 100N) Hands down the best, clearest-speaking, and most engaging professor ever. Awesome sense of humor. She's definitely  concerned with the students' progress and is always available for help. She'll push your thinking and your writing. Good GOD how she'll make you write! She's basically preparing you for grad school.

SHe was alright. Better than Kawamoto. Her lectures were pretty extensive, but if you pay attention, follow along, and take good notes you'll be fine. Tests based on lectures. She did a decent job of relating material to the everyday, which helped with comprehension of the material.

I wasn't sure what this senior seminar as going to be about but it turned out to be the best class I've ever taken. I finally felt like I was being treated like an intelligent adult and I was actually excited about my research project. She really pushed me on my writing but that was good.
She was alright, but I didn't like her teaching method or class (narrative development).  Too much bickering in the class to find it enjoyable.  Not what I expected.
Unbelieveable clear, provides great examples and basis test almost entirely on lectures so show up and its an easy A on the exam. She makes developemental psych kick ass!!!!
I really hate this class. I love the department but this Prof is killing it for me. Make sure to go to lecture and make sure not to fall asleep.
Alright but boring. nice lady
Boring and annoying. I wish she would stay in her ivory tower and quit pretending. I was so excited to get in her course so the disappointment was unreal. Don't take her!
No Comments

I had her for my senior seminar, and i was very much lost with a lot of the materials. She was so incrediably helpful with helping me get on the same page with everyone and help me out with the final paper. Wasn't the easiest class, but i really enjoyed it

Although I had already known some of the material, she presented it in such a way that still made it fun to hear a second or third time.  She has a very good sense of humor and taught the class very well.    In addition, sections were OPTIONAL!

Decent power points.  Terrible when she lectures without them.  WAY too many computer problems!!!  Not totally fair tests.  pretty clear.  Boring text. Very wry sense of humor that really keeps the class entertaining.  "If you don't write that down I'll kill you" -Avril Thorne.  Interesting lady.

I loved this class so much, avril is such a fascinating person. I could listen to her talk about herself all day and still be totally enthralled. I highly recommend this class, I learned a lot about personality just by going to class (I didn't do the reading), and I really enjoyed the final paper!

I liked Avril. She made class interesting with little side stories. She also gives a study guide for the tests. Granted, everything that the class covered is on the study guide but it still helps to make sure everything is studied for when you have a list.  I recommend taking her class

Her class wasn't that hard, she gives you a study guide for the midterm and she lectures using slides, she has witty and humor...altho sometimes it varies but her lectures are entertaining. The only tough part of the class is the final paper where you have to assess a person.
I've had Avril for 3 or 4 classes and she has consistently proven to be well-informed, interested in the students, and capable of teaching a variety of topics -- all with a unique sense of humor.
I had her for a personality Psych lower division. She has a boring teaching style and for some reason she did not like to respond to questions from any men in the class. Hard to approach.
Interesting course, good lectures, projects, tests were easy as long as I had read the material.
class was dry and boring. teacher not very exciting or interesting.
